{
  "stem": "8679.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the day she passed away-- it will be 10 years February 6-- was just about the saddest day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm not lying if I tell you I miss her every day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father had, before he was married, or even maybe when he was married, uh, had studied law in-- today it's called Lviv.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In German, it was called Lemberg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was also in Galicia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the parts that they lived-- it was called in Austria and Poland-- the 'intelligentsia,' quote unquote, spoke German.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when he later came to Vienna, he-- it was difficult to practice law, and so he went into business with two of my uncles, my mother's brothers-- textile.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother was a Jewish mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was at home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Devoting her life to her home, to her children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was strict.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When my mother said no, you knew you didn't have a chance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she was the best.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is one that will stick out in my memory til the day I die.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I say, I was in public school, but the teacher that taught us religion, it was Purim, and she wrote a play for Purim.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, when I went to school in Vienna-- I don't know if has changed-- we were not boys and girls together-- nobody-- nobody.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was strictly separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So obviously the girls had to play boys' roles.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My best friend, Mary Anna-- she was a beautiful girl with long, brown braids-- was obviously Queen Esther.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How I was chosen to play Mordecai, I'm not quite sure.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, my mother gave me a sheet, white sheet, and somehow a golden belt and, of course, a grey beard.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the words that I recited as Mordecai have followed me all my life.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
